    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically robust 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant. This 996.2 iteration delivers power through a 6-speed manual transaxle with precise shift gates. The vehicle features documented preventive maintenance, including a dual-row IMS bearing upgrade and a fresh rear main seal (RMS). The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing McPherson struts forward and a multi-link rear setup for superior lateral stability. Braking is handled by four-piston monobloc calipers over cross-drilled rotors, ensuring minimal fade. The induction note is clean, and the variable valve timing (VarioCam Plus) operates seamlessly across the rev range. A driver-spec example optimized for performance enthusiasts.",
